OL,3,CDoctors and dentists in Wales given 4%
OL,4,Cpay rise as NHS pay awards announced
OL,6,FDoctors and dentists working for the
OL,7,FWelsh NHS will receive a 4% pay rise,
OL,8,Fit has been announced.
OL,10,FOther NHS workers will get a 3.6%
OL,11,Fincrease, with both uplifts above
OL,12,Finflation which currently sits at 3.5%.
OL,14,FWales' health secretary Jeremy Miles
OL,15,Fhas confirmed that both pay awards
OL,16,Fwill be backdated to 1 April this
OL,17,Fyear, with the pay rises are a result
OL,18,Fof recommendations made by the NHS Pay
OL,19,FReview Body (NHSPRB) and the Doctors
OL,20,Fand Dentists Review Body (DDRB) for
OL,21,F2025-26.
