OL,3,CDoctors and dentists in Wales given 4%
OL,4,Cpay rise as NHS pay awards announced
OL,6,FThe increases, recommended by
OL,7,Findependent pay review bodies, are
OL,8,Fabove the rate of inflation, which
OL,9,Fjumped to 3.5% in April, up from 2.6%
OL,10,Fin March and the highest since January
OL,11,F2024.
OL,13,FThese offers are in line with those
OL,14,Fgiven to NHS staff in England.
OL,16,FThe 4% rise will apply to the
OL,17,Ffollowing groups:
OL,19,FStaff who will see the 3.6% rise
OL,20,Finclude nurses, cleaners, porters, and
OL,21,Fhealthcare support workers.
