OL,3,CDoctors and dentists in Wales given 4%
OL,4,Cpay rise as NHS pay awards announced
OL,6,F"I would like to extend my thanks to
OL,7,Fall NHS staff for their ongoing
OL,8,Fdedication and hard work. Your
OL,9,Fcommitment to providing exceptional
OL,10,Fcare and services is truly
OL,11,Fappreciated."
OL,13,FDr Iona Collins, chair of the BMA's
OL,14,FWelsh Council said: "The BMA has
OL,15,Frepeatedly provided evidence to
OL,16,Freflect that NHS Wales doctors are
OL,17,Fundervalued and overworked. The
OL,18,Fpublished pay increase of 1% above
OL,19,Finflation comes nowhere near
OL,20,Faddressing the pay erosion of at least
OL,21,F19% over the last sixteen years.
